summary: This is an email exchange between law enforcement personnel discussing the status of FBI 302 interview reports (specifically for interviews on 2019-12-17 and one from the prior week) related to the Maxwell investigation. The sender explains that the reporting system (Sentinel) is down, delaying the completion of the reports, but attaches recent interview notes and offers to forward a completed 302 once the system is back online.

persons.name: Maxwell
persons.context: The email mentions that supervisors want to meet regarding Maxwell, indicating she is a central subject of the investigation discussed.

events.title: Interview conducted
events.description: An interview was conducted, and a 302 report for it is mentioned as being complete but not yet deliverable due to system issues.

events.title: Email exchange about 302 reports
events.description: Law enforcement personnel communicate about the urgent need for 302 reports from recent interviews for a meeting with supervisors regarding Maxwell.

keyFacts: The email indicates active investigation and interview activity related to Ghislaine Maxwell as of March 2020.
There is urgency from prosecutors to obtain FBI 302 reports from interviews conducted on 2019-12-17 and the week prior to March 2, 2020, for a supervisory meeting.
The FBI's Sentinel reporting system was down for maintenance, causing delays in formalizing interview notes into official 302 reports.
